fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
Let C\xrightarrow {F}Set be any functor. Then the projection functor \text {el}(F)\xrightarrow {\Pi } C from the category of elements strictly creates:
all limits that C admits and F preserves;
all connected colimits that C admits.

fr:frontmatter.fr:meta:
@book{riehl-2017,
  title = {Category Theory in Context},
  author = {Riehl, Emily},
  isbn = {9780486820804},
